</section><div data-type="footnote-refs"><h3 data-type="footnote-refs-title">Footnotes</h3><ul data-list-type="bulleted" data-bullet-style="none"><li data-type="footnote-ref" id="footnote1"><a data-type="footnote-ref-link" href="#footnote-ref1">1</a> <span data-type="footnote-ref-content">This question is taken from the Chemistry Advanced Placement Examination and is used with the permission of the Educational Testing Service.</span></li></ul></div><div data-type="glossary"><h3 data-type="glossary-title">Glossary</h3>
<dl id="fs-idp10319376">
<dt>bond energy</dt>
<dd id="fs-idm69489984">(also, bond dissociation energy) energy required to break a covalent bond in a gaseous substance</dd>
</dl>
<dl id="fs-idp39711472">
<dt>Born-Haber cycle</dt>
<dd id="fs-idp39712112">thermochemical cycle relating the various energetic steps involved in the formation of an ionic solid from the relevant elements</dd>
</dl>
<dl id="fs-idp29295648">
<dt>lattice energy (&#916;<em data-effect="italics">H</em><sub>lattice</sub>)</dt>
<dd id="fs-idm7620624">energy required to separate one mole of an ionic solid into its component gaseous ions</dd>
</dl>
</div></body>

